                        "node": {
                            "id": "MDk6TWlsZXN0b25lMTU3MjE3Ng==",
                            "title": "GitHub export tool",
                            "description": "User story: I can conveniently export my Free Code Camp challenge solutions to GitHub.\r\n\r\nIt is possible to leverage the GitHub API to export the solutions to a repository of user's Choice.\r\n\r\nWorkflow:\r\n1. User \"Clicks Save Solution to GitHub\" button (available only when logged in)\r\n2. If Save button is clicked for first time (Setup the GitHub)\r\n    i. Go through the steps of requesting additional permissions (write access to repository).\r\n    ii. Create a repo \"Free-Code-Camp-Solutions\" (ask user for a name, store it in user object)\r\n    iii. Create a new file for each challenge \"Challenge-Name-Solution-Submission-Date-Time.md\" (let's keep it markdown).\r\n3. If Setup the GitHub is done,\r\n    i. Add a new file as shown above.\r\n    ii. If submitting a second time, that date/time stamped file will automatically handle such scenarios for us.\r\n\r\nLet's keep this flow as simple as we can, we do not need separate challenge category folders to avoid handling renaming them each time our curriculum changes, also we would want campers to be able to save multiple edition of their solutions (time stamped versioned files), so that the on us is on them to delete/keep them later in their repository.",
